issue.title: Refactor
issue.body:
Wrote is_guest method and is_event_planner methods for user model. used those methods on the events controller to limit only guests or event owners to viewing an event page.

Added new methods on locations page to prevent duplicate locations. It works, but not perfectly. If the address is typed a certain way, it doesn't pull the correct id from expedia. hopefully google auto complete  on location form will minimize this.

issue.title: Google places
issue.body:
i altered the create location form so that it will autocomplete and search by the venue/hotel name AND still return the full address.

there are a few minor issues that need to be resolved but i still would like to merge:
1) For whatever reason, the google autocompleted version of "The Nines" hotel is a longer name so it will duplicate. This shouldn't be an issue since this is a seeded location and any additional location inputed the through the form will be consistent since it will autocomplete. 
2) On a very few occasions (the only that i've seen is for The Nines), the expedia API finds a different hotel from the google information and as a result the wrong id is saved
3) when creating a location, the form can be submitted prematurely by hitting "enter/return" and none of the location information is actually saved. form works correctly only when hitting the "create location button"  -- This can probably be solved with some additional event listeners?

issue.title: Maps redo
issue.body: Removed Gmaps gem and redid maps using just the google maps script because gmaps gem could not use autocomplete library and it was causing multiple API call errors. Fixed event autocomplete form event listener so that it would not submit on enter.
